Actress Anita Joseph has criticised local movie practitioners after watching a foreign movie. The film star after watching a ghost seen in a foreign movie compared it with what entails in Nollywood where she belongs. The curvy actress decried how ghosts are portrayed in Nollywood where they are sometimes seen entering tricycles aka ‘keke maruwa’ or even taking pizza to someone.   I’ll rather lick mud than propose to a man –…     Teni lambasts critics dictacting how to spend her money     Yinka Davies to parents: query children’s income   She appealed to the movie practitioners to learn from Hollywood and desist from shooting such pathetic ghost scenes. Sharing a video of the foreign movie ghost scene while she berated Nollywood, ‘mother hen’ said in Pidgin: “Nollywood, how many times did I call you guys? You see as ghost dey appear abi? You see?!”, then she continued in Igbo language Captioning her post, she wrote: “My Nollywood biko kwa nu I no wan Dey see ghost enter keke even bring pizza for person noooo na Mba ekwerom.”